erpretations, ingenious manipulations, and practical applications of natural substances for the benefit of human health. Paul U. Unschuld's annotated translation of the Ben cao gang mu, presented here with the original Chinese text, opens a rare window into viewing the people and culture of China's past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHerbsxTherapeutic usezChinavEarly works to 1800. 0aMateria medicazChinavEarly works to 1800. 0aMedicine, ChinesevEarly works to 1800. 0aNatural historyzChinavPre-Linnean works. 7aMEDICAL / Acupuncture.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520385047?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520385047423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520385047/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099319-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPMb2022